Why this prompt is structured this way
A few specifics worth flagging so you can sanity-check Claude Code's work:
Grep first, move second. The biggest risk in a "delete this folder" cleanup is missing an import somewhere unexpected (a test file, a script, a config). Step 1 forces a full audit before any file moves.
action_parser.py placement. I suggested app/utils/ because it's the standard FastAPI convention for shared helpers and matches your "global things stay shared" principle. If your codebase already has app/core/ or app/common/, Claude Code will use that instead — the prompt allows it.
Absolute over relative imports within workflow files makes it obvious at a glance that rms_tools belongs to rms_workflow (vs. some shared location). When you add SCM later, this consistency pays off.
Verification before deletion. Step 5 must pass before Step 6 runs. The grep for app.agents. after deletion is the final safety net — if anything still references the old path, you'll catch it before runtime errors hit.
